.SH SHMagPowerL
Compute the power of the magnetic field for a single degree \f[CR]l\f[R]
given the Schmidt seminormalized magnetic potential spherical harmonic
coefficients.
.SH Usage
\f[CR]power\f[R] = SHMagPowerL (\f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]a\f[R],
\f[CR]r\f[R], \f[CR]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]power\f[R] : output, real(dp)
The power at degree \f[CR]l\f[R]
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, l+1, l+1)
The Schmidt seminormalized spherical harmonic coefficients of the
magnetic potential.
.TP
\f[CR]a\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The reference radius of the magnetic potential spherical harmonic
coefficients.
.TP
\f[CR]r\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The radius to evaluate the magnetic field.
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree for which the power will be calculated.
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHMagPowerL\f[R] will calculate the power of the magnetic field at
radius \f[CR]r\f[R] for a single degree \f[CR]l\f[R] given the magnetic
potential Schmidt seminormalized spherical harmonic coefficients
\f[CR]c\f[R] evaluated at radius \f[CR]a\f[R].
This is explicitly calculated as:
.PP
\f[CR]S(l) = (l+1) (a/r)**(2l+4) Sum_{m=0}\(hal [ cilm(1, l+1, m+1)**2 + cilm(2, l+1, m+1)**2 ].\f[R]
